Hi Jimmy,

Can you please run the below query against the DB and share the results with me?

SELECT  COUNT(ID) TotalResources FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAA_Resources];

SELECT  COUNT(ID) TotalEvents FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAC_ActivityEvents];
SELECT  COUNT(FolderID) TotalDailyActivities FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAC_DailyActivity];

SELECT COUNT(ID) OrphanEvents
FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAC_ActivityEvents] AE
WHERE NOT EXISTS
(
    SELECT 1
    FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAA_Resources] R
    WHERE R.Host = AE.Host AND R.Id = AE.PathID
);

SELECT COUNT(FolderID) OrphanDailyActivities
FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAC_DailyActivity] A
WHERE NOT EXISTS
(
    SELECT 1
    FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAA_Resources] R
    WHERE R.Host = A.Host AND R.Id = A.FolderID
);

I was asking for the job so I can identify what was difference between a working job (My lab) and the job that was throwing error.

Please run the maintenance repair tool on the FSAC bulk import and let me know if you're still experiencing the same issue. Please ensure that no file system jobs run while the repair is in progress. Repairs sometimes require 2 or 3 runs to catch all the necessary issues.

FSAA: Query Selection

If you select FSAC bulk import job > select queries > query properties > click configure > click maintenance button > select repair > select ok > and run.

SELECT  COUNT(ID) TotalResources FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAA_Resources];

(

    FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAA_Resources] R
    WHERE R.Host = AE.Host AND R.Id = AE.PathID
);

FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAC_DailyActivity] A
WHERE NOT EXISTS
(
    SELECT 1
    FROM [dbo].[SA_FSAA_Resources] R
    WHERE R.Host = A.Host AND R.Id = A.FolderID
);
